  "title": "CurrentRefinements with Range widgets will show two items instead of one",
  "body": "<!--\r\n  Thanks for participating in this project! We will try to answer as soon as possible 🙏\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe 🙏**\r\n\r\nUsing CurrentRefinement with a range widget, you will get two separate refinements listed, but realistically only both can be cleared at the same time, since as soon as you touch a range, it should be cleared on both sides\r\n\r\n**Describe the solution you'd like 🤔**\r\n\r\nThe range widget to clarify to the current refinements that those two ranges should be considered as a single one.\r\n\r\n**Describe alternatives you've considered ✨**\r\n\r\nSome way where we base current refinements off the widgets, instead of the helper state would help in issues like this and #3346 \r\n",
